'''Marie Clémentine Dusabejambo''' (wavutse 1987) ni umukinnyi wa firime wo mu [[Rwanda]].

== Ubuzima ==
Dusabejambo yavukiye i [[Kigali]] muri 1987, <ref name="Kagire">Linda M. Kagire, [https://www.newtimes.co.rw/entertainment/fespaco-nyirasafari-highlights FESPACO recap: Nyirasafari highlights government efforts to boost film industry], ''The New Times'', March 1, 2019.</ref> umwuga we ni ukuba enjeniyeri w'amashanyarazi n'itumanaho. <ref name="Dia">Thierno I. Dia, [http://www.africine.org/?menu=fiche&no=32417 Dusabejambo Clémentine], africine.org, May 7, 2019.</ref>

Filime ngufi ya ''Dusabejambo , Lyiza'' yatsindiye igihembo cya bronze cya Tanit mu iserukiramuco rya Filime rya Carthage mu 2012. <ref name="Kagire">Linda M. Kagire, [https://www.newtimes.co.rw/entertainment/fespaco-nyirasafari-highlights FESPACO recap: Nyirasafari highlights government efforts to boost film industry], ''The New Times'', March 1, 2019.</ref> Filime ye ngufi ''A Place for Myself'' (2016) yavuze amateka y'umukobwa ukiri muto ukomoka mu [[Rwanda]] urwaye albinism, uhanganye n’ivangura n’agasuzuguro yakorewe mu ishuri ribanza. <ref name="Toronto">Moses Opobo, [https://www.newtimes.co.rw/section/read/207804 Rwandan film selected for Toronto Black Film Festival], ''[[The New Times (Rwanda)|The New Times]]'', February 8, 2017.</ref> Dusabejambo yashimishijwe niyi ngingo nyuma yo kumva amakuru y’ubwicanyi bwakorewe abantu barwaye alibinism muri [[Tanzaniya]] . <ref>Stephanie Jason, [https://mg.co.za/article/2017-03-24-00-the-rise-of-rwandas-women-filmmakers The rise of Rwanda’s women filmmakers], ''[[Mail & Guardian]]'', March 24, 2017.</ref> Iyi filime yerekanwe bwa mbere muri Goethe Institut i [[Kigali]], <ref name="OnScooping">Moses Opobo, [https://www.newtimes.co.rw/section/read/208808 Dusabejambo on scooping Thomas Sankara Prize at FESPACO], ''The New Times'', March 12, 2017.</ref> kandi yerekanwe mu iserukiramuco rya Filime ryabirabura rya Toronto 2017. <ref name="Toronto" /> Yabonye ibihembo bitatu, harimo igihembo cya Ousmane Sembene, mu iserukiramuco mpuzamahanga rya sinema rya Zanzibar (ZIFF), <ref name="OnScooping" /> kandi yegukanye igihembo cya bronze cya Tanit mu iserukiramuco rya sinema rya Carthage mu 2016. <ref name="Kagire" /> Yatowe kandi muri Filime Nziza  mu bihembo bya [[Afurika]]  bya Filime 2017, <ref name="Iribagazia">Glory Iribagazia, [https://www.newtimes.co.rw/entertainment/rwandan-film-nominated-eight-amaa-awards Rwandan film nominated for eight AMAA awards], ''The New Times'', September 21, 2019.</ref> kandi yegukanye igihembo cya Thomas Sankara muri FESPACO 2017. <ref>Moses Opobo, [https://www.newtimes.co.rw/section/read/208671 Rwandan film scoops two prestigious awards at FESPACO], ''The New Times'', March 8, 2017.</ref> <ref name="OnScooping" />

''Icyasha'' (2018) yibanze kumuhungu wimyaka 12, wifuzaga kwinjira mumakipe y'umupira w'amaguru  ariko akaba atotezwa kubera effeminate. <ref>Moses Opobo, [https://www.newtimes.co.rw/lifestyle/rwandan-movies-nominated-ziff-2018-awards Rwandan movies nominated for ZIFF 2018 awards], ''The New Times'', July 10, 2018.</ref> Yatowe muri Filime Nziza  muri ZIFF 2018, <ref name="Iribagazia">Glory Iribagazia, [https://www.newtimes.co.rw/entertainment/rwandan-film-nominated-eight-amaa-awards Rwandan film nominated for eight AMAA awards], ''The New Times'', September 21, 2019.</ref> mu cyiciro cya firime ngufi mu iserukiramuco rya Filime rya Carthage, <ref>Moses Opobo, [https://www.newtimes.co.rw/entertainment/three-rwandan-films-competition-carthage-film-festival Three Rwandan films in competition at Carthage Film Festival], ''The New Times'', November 6, 2018.</ref> no muri Filime ngufi nziza muri [[Afurika]] muri Movie Academy Awards 2019. <ref name="Iribagazia" /> Yatsindiye igihembo cya Zébu muri Filime ngufi ya Panafrican muri Rencontres du Film Court Madagascar 2019. <ref name="Dia">Thierno I. Dia, [http://www.africine.org/?menu=fiche&no=32417 Dusabejambo Clémentine], africine.org, May 7, 2019.</ref>

